body.txt: lack of server space – the win space should be dropping.
There is No throttling. Throttling happens when there is a lack of server space – and this would cause the win space to drop.
There are no retransmissions. Retransmissions happens when a server acks for a sequence number twice. It is also possible to manually check the TCP graph for retransmission.
At the beginning the server acks every packet and each packet is of size 1460. However, after around packet 67 we send two packets (total size 2920) but we only ack once.
Server determines the seq # as random and the ack # as the seq # from client + 1
Both hosts initiated the close/Fin. This is a Simultaneous close. We know this because given that
F F A A – means that close was initiated by both hosts. ←And this is what we see in the table
F A F A – means that close was initiated by one host.
